  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      As of today there is very limited scientific knowledge in whicj of the two vascular access
      devices (PICC-line or venous ports) that offers the lowest complicationrates in
      cancerpatients. The study group wants to clearify this unsolved matter by comparing the two
      systems. Our primary endpoint is the presens of catheter related venous thrombosis. We are
      also looking at all catheter related complications and patient satisfaction.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
